    "In the code block below, we define two sets of coordinates (two points) in two-dimensional space. Their coordinates are x1,y1 and x2,y2 respectively. \n",
    "\n",
    "Calculate and ```print()``` their euclidean distance.\n",
    "\n",
    "Euclidean distance (let's call it d) between two points is calculated as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"img/euclid.png\" width=\"200\"/>\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: the answer is approximately 8.06."
   ]
  },
  {
