    "### Exercise 5.5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Suppose you want to generate a random integer between 1 and 10 (1 and 10 both included), but from the `random` module you only have the `random()` function available. How do you do that?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 518,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "4\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Generate a random integer using only random()\n",
    "from random import random\n",
    "random_float = random()\n",
    "print(int(random_float*10 + 1))\n",
    "# at first i had just int(random_float*10, but that would never generate 10;\n",
    "# +0.1 was tried but that didn't work, +1 did the trick"
   ]
